I prefer scenario 2, although it may bring challenges. AI has a huge impact, involving not only technical issues, but also social ethics, fairness and global impact. If only experts, boards and companies themselves make decisions, the needs of ordinary people may be ignored, and even the existing power structure may be strengthened. Including different perspectives, including the opinions of non-professionals, can ensure that AI development is in the broader social interest, rather than just serving companies or elite groups. 

But AI is not a neutral tool, it affects everyone. Therefore, involving people from different backgrounds in decision-making, although complex, can make AI fairer and more inclusive. 
For AI, we hope that it can become a tool for ordinary people to further have a voice rather than a tool for those in power to further consolidate their position.
